# Backend NestJS Rules
- Use one module per business domain with standard module/controller/service/dto organization.
- Validate every inbound DTO with `class-validator` and transform inputs deliberately.
- Use Prisma only through approved services; never scatter ad-hoc database access across controllers.
- Wrap order, payment, stock, loyalty, and courier assignment mutations in transactions when atomicity matters.
- Use centralized exception filters, shared error codes, guards, decorators, and response interceptors.
- Use role guards for broad access and permission guards for sensitive actions; enforce ownership checks in services.
- Offload slow or retryable work to queues instead of blocking requests.
- Document endpoints with Swagger/OpenAPI and keep contracts aligned with DTOs.
- Keep modules loosely coupled and avoid circular dependencies.
